{
  "stem": "25598.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But on Friday, Friday, late afternoon, there was a tradition that everybody would go to the steam bath, which was not too far from us.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we called it the shvitz.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And shvitz meaning, perspiring, sweating, and there you go.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The steam bath, you sweat.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I did not like that at all, but everybody went.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So I went, too.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I didn't like it, number one because I couldn't breathe well because of the steam, and because I had to be in the nude.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I-- that-- even though we were just the women, separate, of course-- but I still didn't like to expose my body.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So I didn't like it, but I had to go.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And then we came home, and then it was dinner with singing.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we usually had guests.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And then my father always went to shul, to the temple.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Sometimes I did, sometimes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Fri-- Saturday mornings I went more than Friday night, because Friday night I helped my mother clean up.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there was a routine to everything we did.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was-- it was almost like there was nothing unexpected in that life.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Everybody knew what tomorrow is going to be like, or what next week is going to be like, or when the tourists are going to come, or when the music is going to start to play in the park in the gazebos for the tourists.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And those Romania-- I don't know if in all of Romania, but where we lived-- the four seasons were absolutely three months, each season.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So come March the 1st, we were actually wearing a little brooch with some red and white ribbons, to signify the, the coming of spring.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that was when we put away the winter clothes.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it was spring.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
